{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:psalms.74",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 74,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 74 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:1",
      "text": "God, why have you rejected us forever? Why does your anger smolder against the sheep of your pasture?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:2",
      "text": "Remember your congregation, which you purchased of old, which you have redeemed to be the tribe of your inheritance: Mount Zion, in which you have lived.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:3",
      "text": "Lift up your feet to the perpetual ruins, all the evil that the enemy has done in the sanctuary.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:4",
      "text": "Your adversaries have roared in the middle of your assembly. They have set up their standards as signs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:5",
      "text": "They behaved like men wielding axes, cutting through a thicket of trees.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:6",
      "text": "Now they break all its carved work down with hatchet and hammers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:7",
      "text": "They have burned your sanctuary to the ground. They have profaned the dwelling place of your Name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:8",
      "text": "They said in their heart, “ We will crush them completely.” They have burned up all the places in the land where God was worshiped.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:9",
      "text": "We see no miraculous signs. There is no longer any prophet, neither is there among us anyone who knows how long.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:10",
      "text": "How long, God, shall the adversary reproach? Shall the enemy blaspheme your name forever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:11",
      "text": "Why do you draw back your hand, even your right hand? Take it from your chest and consume them!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:12",
      "text": "Yet God is my King of old, working salvation throughout the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:13",
      "text": "You divided the sea by your strength. You broke the heads of the sea monsters in the waters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:14",
      "text": "You broke the heads of Leviathan in pieces. You gave him as food to people and desert creatures.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:15",
      "text": "You opened up spring and stream. You dried up mighty rivers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:16",
      "text": "The day is yours, the night is also yours. You have prepared the light and the sun.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:17",
      "text": "You have set all the boundaries of the earth. You have made summer and winter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:18",
      "text": "Remember this, that the enemy has mocked you, Yahweh. Foolish people have blasphemed your name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:19",
      "text": "Don’t deliver the soul of your dove to wild beasts. Don’t forget the life of your poor forever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:20",
      "text": "Honor your covenant, for haunts of violence fill the dark places of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:21",
      "text": "Don’t let the oppressed return ashamed. Let the poor and needy praise your name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:22",
      "text": "Arise, God! Plead your own cause. Remember how the foolish man mocks you all day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.74.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:23",
      "text": "Don’t forget the voice of your adversaries. The tumult of those who rise up against you ascends continually.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
